1
00:00:09,030 --> 00:00:11,365
[Baek-jeong breathes deeply]

2
00:00:12,033 --> 00:00:14,118
Give me four days
and I can arrange the flight.

3
00:00:14,744 --> 00:00:16,746
[tense music playing]

4
00:00:17,997 --> 00:00:19,373
So, where are we going?

5
00:00:19,457 --> 00:00:21,584
I'm thinking maybe Thailand or Vietnam,

6
00:00:21,667 --> 00:00:25,087
but it might be easier for you in Thailand
because you know people there.

7
00:00:25,171 --> 00:00:26,005
Yeah.

8
00:00:27,673 --> 00:00:29,759
I'll go through and make the arrangements.

9
00:00:29,842 --> 00:00:33,763
I'd also recommend
some S-class bloodhounds.

10
00:00:34,430 --> 00:00:36,557
If you have three,
then that should get the job done.

11
00:00:36,640 --> 00:00:37,975
That is

12
00:00:38,559 --> 00:00:41,187
if you're trying
to kidnap Kim Gun-woo's mother.

13
00:00:41,854 --> 00:00:42,855
How much?

14
00:00:42,938 --> 00:00:45,816
300 million each. So 900 million.

15
00:00:46,400 --> 00:00:47,401
[chuckles softly]

16
00:00:47,985 --> 00:00:50,112
[Man-bae] You're wanted
and we don't have much time.

17
00:00:50,196 --> 00:00:52,073
We have to do this the right way.

18
00:00:52,156 --> 00:00:53,449
It's a

19
00:00:54,575 --> 00:00:55,868
necessary investment.

20
00:00:56,535 --> 00:00:58,245
S-class is special,

21
00:00:58,913 --> 00:01:01,165
I promise you with my life,

22
00:01:02,500 --> 00:01:05,503
because they'll do the job right.

23
00:01:08,380 --> 00:01:11,175
Get us two, would ya? You're number three.

24
00:01:15,012 --> 00:01:15,930
I understand.

25
00:01:16,430 --> 00:01:17,515
[music fades]

26
00:01:18,099 --> 00:01:19,600
-[phone buzzing]
-Who's that?

27
00:01:20,768 --> 00:01:21,811
It's just my mother.

28
00:01:22,561 --> 00:01:23,395
Then take it.

29
00:01:26,774 --> 00:01:28,692
-Hey.
-[mother] Where are you right now?

30
00:01:28,776 --> 00:01:30,778
-Why?
-Min-a got hit by a car.

31
00:01:30,861 --> 00:01:32,863
What? How bad is it?

32
00:01:33,531 --> 00:01:36,200
-Where are you?
-The ER at Seonkuk University Medical.

33
00:01:36,283 --> 00:01:38,744
-Hurry up and get here.
-Got it.

34
00:01:39,453 --> 00:01:41,455
[tense music playing]

35
00:01:42,748 --> 00:01:45,417
My daughter was hit by a car.
They're at the hospital.

36
00:01:53,342 --> 00:01:54,301
Go then.

37
00:02:03,144 --> 00:02:05,771
[breathes shakily]

38
00:02:06,522 --> 00:02:08,357
[tires screeching]

39
00:02:25,416 --> 00:02:26,876
Show me your ID, please.

40
00:02:28,043 --> 00:02:30,462
[Tae-geom breathes shakily] Just a second.

41
00:02:31,505 --> 00:02:33,591
-And the name of the patient?
-Yun Min-a.

42
00:02:33,674 --> 00:02:36,677
Okay, come on in.
Room's around the corner and to the left.

43
00:02:37,469 --> 00:02:39,805
[panting]

44
00:02:45,311 --> 00:02:46,145
Min-a.

45
00:02:47,229 --> 00:02:48,522
Oh, Dad!

46
00:02:49,148 --> 00:02:50,733
I need you all in position.

47
00:02:55,905 --> 00:02:56,739
Are you okay?

48
00:02:57,323 --> 00:02:58,240
Huh?

49
00:03:00,993 --> 00:03:02,578
Listen to me.

50
00:03:03,078 --> 00:03:05,372
Please stop doing this.

51
00:03:06,707 --> 00:03:07,583
[gasps]

52
00:03:08,417 --> 00:03:09,835
Tae-geom. Tae-geom!

53
00:03:11,587 --> 00:03:12,755
That's enough. Hey, stop!

54
00:03:14,173 --> 00:03:16,342
Hey, hey, hey, hey. Put the guns down.

55
00:03:16,425 --> 00:03:18,052
-Put the guns down.
-Min-a.

56
00:03:19,094 --> 00:03:20,721
Close your eyes and hold on tight.

57
00:03:21,472 --> 00:03:23,098
[Gang-yong] It's all right. Put them down.

58
00:03:28,938 --> 00:03:31,273
Hey! Put them down. It's okay.

59
00:03:32,733 --> 00:03:33,651
It's okay.

60
00:03:38,781 --> 00:03:40,074
Tae-geom, hey.

61
00:03:40,783 --> 00:03:41,951
We're not gonna hurt you.

62
00:03:44,578 --> 00:03:45,621
Let's just talk.

63
00:03:46,622 --> 00:03:49,250
I promise, I'm really just here
to talk to you.

64
00:03:54,755 --> 00:03:55,798
[sighs]

65
00:03:55,881 --> 00:03:58,968
I also have a young daughter.

66
00:04:01,762 --> 00:04:03,222
From one dad to another,

67
00:04:04,056 --> 00:04:05,516
let's just talk about it.

68
00:04:10,604 --> 00:04:12,606
[water running]

69
00:04:14,066 --> 00:04:16,068
[suspenseful music playing]

70
00:04:23,325 --> 00:04:24,660
Sir, what brings you in?

71
00:04:29,999 --> 00:04:32,501
A guest sent by your uncle
has arrived, sir.

72
00:04:40,843 --> 00:04:41,844
[music fades]

73
00:04:42,511 --> 00:04:44,680
I want to thank you for coming here.

74
00:04:52,604 --> 00:04:54,398
Nice to meet you. I'm Choi Sin-hyeong.

75
00:04:54,481 --> 00:04:55,649
[tense music playing]

76
00:04:57,276 --> 00:04:59,862
Hmm. I know the name's a bit unusual.

77
00:05:00,863 --> 00:05:02,406
It's a code name I go by.

78
00:05:05,451 --> 00:05:07,119
[tense electronic music playing]

79
00:05:33,312 --> 00:05:35,856
BLOODHOUNDS 2

80
00:05:36,357 --> 00:05:37,316
[music fades]

81
00:05:39,777 --> 00:05:43,447
If they were to bring you in, you'd get
a life sentence or the death penalty.

82
00:05:43,530 --> 00:05:46,950
If you help us, I'll do my very best
to get you the life sentence.

83
00:05:47,034 --> 00:05:49,495
-[uneasy music playing]
-And what would be the point of that?

84
00:05:49,578 --> 00:05:53,832
If you're sentenced to death, you won't
be able to have visitors or seek parole.

85
00:05:53,916 --> 00:05:56,835
But with a life sentence,
it could be possible to get parole,

86
00:05:57,336 --> 00:05:58,587
assuming that you're good.

87
00:05:59,922 --> 00:06:01,924
[sighs]

88
00:06:05,928 --> 00:06:07,262
Yun Tae-geom, sir.

89
00:06:08,722 --> 00:06:10,057
I mean, bro.

90
00:06:11,642 --> 00:06:15,396
Didn't you start working under
Im Baek-jeong to provide for your family?

91
00:06:16,397 --> 00:06:19,483
[chuckles] Well, then, you should do
whatever it takes

92
00:06:19,566 --> 00:06:21,902
so you can live
to protect your mother and daughter.

93
00:06:22,528 --> 00:06:26,824
Your family? They're never gonna give up
on you, no matter how much you screw up.

94
00:06:26,907 --> 00:06:28,242
And your mother?

95
00:06:28,742 --> 00:06:31,954
That woman would do almost anything
to save her child, even if it kills her.

96
00:06:32,037 --> 00:06:33,956
You know that. And your daughter?

97
00:06:34,456 --> 00:06:39,962
Hey, man, your daughter, I bet she'd wait
her whole fucking life just to see you.

98
00:06:40,587 --> 00:06:43,841
But man, "the point?" [scoffs]

99
00:06:44,341 --> 00:06:47,219
You can't see the point? Is that it, huh?

100
00:06:47,719 --> 00:06:49,721
Is that the type of dad that they need?

101
00:06:50,889 --> 00:06:51,723
Fine, then.

102
00:06:52,433 --> 00:06:53,475
Be that guy.

103
00:06:57,104 --> 00:06:57,938
Tae-geom, please.

104
00:06:59,481 --> 00:07:01,442
It's not over until it's over.

105
00:07:02,317 --> 00:07:05,070
We could still do more for each other.
I'm sure of it.

106
00:07:05,571 --> 00:07:07,781
[tense music playing]

107
00:07:07,865 --> 00:07:09,283
So, how about you join us?

108
00:07:15,831 --> 00:07:17,166
[Tae-geom exhales]

109
00:07:18,959 --> 00:07:21,670
Keep my family safe from Im Baek-jeong.

110
00:07:24,173 --> 00:07:25,466
I promise you that.

111
00:07:27,509 --> 00:07:28,510
[exhales]

112
00:07:29,928 --> 00:07:31,054
What do you want me to say?

113
00:07:32,347 --> 00:07:34,975
Well, first, where is Im Baek-jeong?

114
00:07:35,476 --> 00:07:37,686
He's on the move,
aboard his yacht on the Han River.

115
00:07:38,770 --> 00:07:40,647
If I contact him,
he'll tell me the pickup point.

116
00:07:40,731 --> 00:07:43,525
The yacht could be docking
at one of three positions.

117
00:07:45,152 --> 00:07:46,528
He's a smart guy.

118
00:07:49,156 --> 00:07:50,532
How about we raid them tonight?

119
00:07:50,616 --> 00:07:52,826
If by chance we fail to arrest him,

120
00:07:52,910 --> 00:07:54,995
won't Tae-geom be in danger?

121
00:07:55,579 --> 00:07:58,248
How about we maintain his cover
and wait for the right opportunity?

122
00:07:59,416 --> 00:08:01,627
We could. You're right.

123
00:08:03,337 --> 00:08:06,882
But, um, how did he know
we would be raiding the Entra Hotel?

124
00:08:06,965 --> 00:08:09,301
I believe he was informed by an employee.

125
00:08:09,384 --> 00:08:10,427
[exhales]

126
00:08:11,053 --> 00:08:12,596
Lots of people in his circle, then?

127
00:08:12,679 --> 00:08:13,764
Yes.

128
00:08:14,264 --> 00:08:16,767
Who's organizing all this for him?
That's what I need from you.

129
00:08:16,850 --> 00:08:19,311
Could it… could it be a cop?

130
00:08:19,394 --> 00:08:22,523
There's a guy called Lee Dong-hyeon.
He was an NIS agent.

131
00:08:25,734 --> 00:08:26,818
Lee Man-bae, right?

132
00:08:27,402 --> 00:08:28,987
His actual name is Lee Dong-hyeon.

133
00:08:29,071 --> 00:08:31,865
Is he the one
who gave the order to kill Gi-na?

134
00:08:31,949 --> 00:08:32,908
Yes.

135
00:08:33,408 --> 00:08:35,118
So, who in the police force
does he control?

136
00:08:35,202 --> 00:08:36,828
I'm not sure yet.

137
00:08:37,871 --> 00:08:39,665
I know for sure there was more than one.

138
00:08:39,748 --> 00:08:41,667
I could hear that much
from his phone call.

139
00:08:42,251 --> 00:08:43,794
He's a meticulous man.

140
00:08:44,461 --> 00:08:46,922
Then it's possible he could have heard
about the wanted alert.

141
00:08:48,173 --> 00:08:50,384
Lee Dong-hyeon's looking
for a private plane.

142
00:08:50,884 --> 00:08:52,344
I'll bet you he's going to Thailand.

143
00:08:54,263 --> 00:08:56,181
He couldn't do that with a warrant though.

144
00:08:56,265 --> 00:08:58,642
He's the kind of man
that would make it happen.

145
00:08:59,268 --> 00:09:00,185
[scoffs]

146
00:09:01,353 --> 00:09:02,604
Our goal

147
00:09:03,981 --> 00:09:06,984
is to capture Kim Gun-woo's mother
and take her to Thailand.

148
00:09:07,067 --> 00:09:09,486
Im Baek-jeong wants
to fight Kim Gun-woo again.

149
00:09:10,320 --> 00:09:12,447
So he plans to kidnap his mother
to lure him in.

150
00:09:12,531 --> 00:09:13,740
For ransom money?

151
00:09:14,658 --> 00:09:17,869
It seems that Baek-jeong
has a more personal reason.

152
00:09:18,704 --> 00:09:22,165
I think he believes he lost to Kim Gun-woo
in that previous fight they had.

153
00:09:23,875 --> 00:09:27,296
Because viewers all over the world
rooted for Kim Gun-woo to win.

154
00:09:28,755 --> 00:09:30,382
So while everyone's watching,

155
00:09:32,259 --> 00:09:33,760
Kim Gun-woo's going to be killed.

156
00:09:35,304 --> 00:09:37,014
Gun-woo's gonna what?

157
00:09:39,308 --> 00:09:41,935
There are a few ways to fight in the IKFC.

158
00:09:42,019 --> 00:09:44,062
One of those is a death match.

159
00:09:44,896 --> 00:09:46,607
They fight until one of them dies.

160
00:09:47,316 --> 00:09:49,401
That's the fight
that makes the most money.

161
00:09:49,484 --> 00:09:52,446
So kidnapping Gun-woo's mother.
How's he doing it?

162
00:09:52,529 --> 00:09:54,698
Dong-hyeon is paying S-class bloodhounds.

163
00:09:54,781 --> 00:09:55,657
What's that?

164
00:09:56,825 --> 00:09:59,036
They're professional killers for hire.

165
00:09:59,119 --> 00:10:03,957
The S-class means that Dong-hyeon's people
are as deadly as they could be.

166
00:10:04,541 --> 00:10:08,128
So then, do you think he also knows
where Gun-woo's mother is staying?

167
00:10:09,671 --> 00:10:10,589
I don't have a clue.

168
00:10:10,672 --> 00:10:12,215
It wasn't ever mentioned?

169
00:10:14,092 --> 00:10:15,093
No.

170
00:10:16,094 --> 00:10:17,220
[Gang-yong sighs]

171
00:10:17,971 --> 00:10:18,972
[phone buzzing]

172
00:10:19,056 --> 00:10:20,515
PRESIDENT

173
00:10:21,391 --> 00:10:22,225
Im Baek-jeong?

174
00:10:24,311 --> 00:10:28,315
Let's tell him that Min-a hurt her head
and she's waiting for a scan right now.

175
00:10:33,654 --> 00:10:34,821
[Tae-geom] Sir.

176
00:10:34,905 --> 00:10:36,031
[Baek-jeong] How is she?

177
00:10:36,114 --> 00:10:39,660
She hit her head pretty bad on the ground.
She's gonna get a CT scan.

178
00:10:45,832 --> 00:10:48,377
-[Baek-jeong] Wrap it up and get back.
-Okay.

179
00:10:49,419 --> 00:10:50,295
[sighs]

180
00:10:51,463 --> 00:10:52,464
[Gang-yong] Tae-geom.

181
00:10:54,257 --> 00:10:55,926
[tense music builds]

182
00:11:03,600 --> 00:11:04,601
[music fades]

183
00:11:04,685 --> 00:11:06,728
-[nurse] Kim Jin-su, please come in.
-[man] Okay.

184
00:11:10,357 --> 00:11:13,485
The wound is healing well,
so you don't have anything to worry about.

185
00:11:13,568 --> 00:11:14,653
I appreciate it.

186
00:11:20,158 --> 00:11:21,284
How's your shoulder?

187
00:11:21,368 --> 00:11:23,912
Um, it hurts a little.

188
00:11:24,413 --> 00:11:25,497
Could I see it?

189
00:11:29,835 --> 00:11:30,877
[Gun-woo winces]

190
00:11:32,170 --> 00:11:33,463
Do you need painkillers?

191
00:11:35,048 --> 00:11:36,049
I'll be okay.

192
00:11:36,883 --> 00:11:37,926
[doctor] All right, then.

193
00:11:51,815 --> 00:11:52,691
Min-beom.

194
00:11:56,069 --> 00:11:57,404
How's it going?

195
00:11:58,613 --> 00:12:00,198
This room is so small.

196
00:12:00,824 --> 00:12:02,200
You want me to upgrade you?

197
00:12:03,034 --> 00:12:06,121
Oh, no, this room's already
too much for me, but thanks anyway.

198
00:12:06,705 --> 00:12:08,582
I'm going to the hospital
to visit Gang-yong.

199
00:12:08,665 --> 00:12:11,543
-Could you let me come?
-No, you shouldn't.

200
00:12:12,753 --> 00:12:14,254
I'll talk to him and call you.

201
00:12:16,757 --> 00:12:17,966
Just rest up.

202
00:12:18,675 --> 00:12:19,551
Okay.

203
00:12:19,634 --> 00:12:21,636
[tense music playing]

204
00:12:25,098 --> 00:12:26,099
[music fades]

205
00:12:32,814 --> 00:12:34,941
[breathes deeply]

206
00:12:36,318 --> 00:12:38,028
[mysterious music playing]

207
00:12:38,987 --> 00:12:40,989
Seul-gi, have you thought
about your code name?

208
00:12:41,573 --> 00:12:42,908
I haven't thought of anything yet.

209
00:12:44,075 --> 00:12:45,994
You know, your look is delicate,

210
00:12:46,077 --> 00:12:48,747
so it's important
that you pick a strong name.

211
00:12:49,414 --> 00:12:52,334
Something like… Jung Hwa-gi.

212
00:12:54,252 --> 00:12:55,170
Jung Hwa-gi?

213
00:12:59,883 --> 00:13:02,344
-You don't like it?
-It'd be an honor.

214
00:13:05,388 --> 00:13:06,306
I'm just joking.

215
00:13:06,389 --> 00:13:08,850
-[exhales]
-[Sin-hyeong] What kind of name is Hwa-gi?

216
00:13:12,062 --> 00:13:13,230
How about Kang Ryeok-han?

217
00:13:16,107 --> 00:13:17,025
Ryeok-han?

218
00:13:19,027 --> 00:13:19,861
Mm.

219
00:13:23,782 --> 00:13:24,783
Incredible.

220
00:13:26,409 --> 00:13:28,787
I'm good at making code names.

221
00:13:31,039 --> 00:13:32,290
[phone chimes and buzzes]

222
00:13:36,127 --> 00:13:36,962
Hello?

223
00:13:37,546 --> 00:13:39,631
-The meeting's about to start.
-[Sin-hyeong] All right.

224
00:13:39,714 --> 00:13:41,883
[tense music playing]

225
00:13:42,717 --> 00:13:45,262
HONG MIN-BEOM
PRESIDENT OF IIL GROUP

226
00:13:45,345 --> 00:13:48,974
We'll have two chances.
When they come to kidnap Gun-woo's mother.

227
00:13:49,474 --> 00:13:51,560
And when they get off the yacht
to flee abroad.

228
00:13:52,978 --> 00:13:54,980
Is this person trustworthy?

229
00:13:55,063 --> 00:13:56,398
Yun Tae-geom?

230
00:13:57,357 --> 00:14:00,735
-We'd say he's worthy of your trust.
-Hmm. I agree with that.

231
00:14:01,403 --> 00:14:04,114
How about Gun-woo's mother? Is she safe?

232
00:14:04,197 --> 00:14:06,241
[Gang-yong] Well, we did
talk about that too.

233
00:14:06,324 --> 00:14:08,159
Where she's at now is the safest.

234
00:14:08,243 --> 00:14:10,287
Woo-jin and Woo-jeong
will stay at the hotel

235
00:14:10,370 --> 00:14:11,955
and they have guards to keep her safe.

236
00:14:12,956 --> 00:14:14,749
[Min-beom] So if they're after his mother,

237
00:14:16,001 --> 00:14:17,127
does Gun-woo know?

238
00:14:17,752 --> 00:14:21,006
He doesn't know. Gun-woo wouldn't
think twice about leaving the hospital.

239
00:14:21,673 --> 00:14:22,883
Probably, yeah.

240
00:14:24,593 --> 00:14:28,179
I'd like it if he could just focus
on his recovery.

241
00:14:28,889 --> 00:14:31,308
I believe we can ensure
his mother's safety.

242
00:14:31,850 --> 00:14:34,895
It'll be more dangerous
if Gun-woo fights in his current state.

243
00:14:35,395 --> 00:14:37,397
[poignant music playing]

244
00:14:38,189 --> 00:14:39,232
So…

245
00:14:41,276 --> 00:14:43,111
what do we do once we catch 'em?

246
00:14:43,945 --> 00:14:44,821
Hmm?

247
00:14:47,532 --> 00:14:48,700
[chuckles]

248
00:14:50,744 --> 00:14:52,370
Punish them to the fullest legal extent.

249
00:14:54,372 --> 00:14:56,207
That doesn't feel like enough.

250
00:14:56,291 --> 00:14:58,668
I'm still anxious
with Kim Myeong-gil behind bars.

251
00:14:58,752 --> 00:15:00,670
We need something… more.

252
00:15:02,589 --> 00:15:04,341
So then how do you wanna deal with it?

253
00:15:06,384 --> 00:15:07,844
[Min-beom] Could you excuse us?

254
00:15:08,345 --> 00:15:09,930
No, Gwang-mu, it's okay.

255
00:15:11,598 --> 00:15:12,974
It's okay. Just say it.

256
00:15:16,102 --> 00:15:17,062
[music fades]

257
00:15:21,358 --> 00:15:22,317
I want him dead.

258
00:15:22,817 --> 00:15:25,111
[tense music playing]

259
00:15:25,820 --> 00:15:26,821
My uncle

260
00:15:27,530 --> 00:15:29,157
assigned some agents to me.

261
00:15:31,660 --> 00:15:32,911
[Gang-yong] What kind of agents?

262
00:15:33,912 --> 00:15:34,871
Black ops.

263
00:15:36,915 --> 00:15:40,877
[exhales] This issue is ours. There's
no reason for the NIS to get involved.

264
00:15:40,961 --> 00:15:43,672
-Well, can you kill these guys?
-[Gang-yong] Min-beom.

265
00:15:44,297 --> 00:15:48,385
We have to… let them
spend the rest of their lives in jail,

266
00:15:48,468 --> 00:15:49,719
reflecting on what they've done,

267
00:15:49,803 --> 00:15:52,722
and return all that stolen wealth
back to society.

268
00:15:53,306 --> 00:15:54,182
Do you understand?

269
00:15:58,645 --> 00:16:01,147
I need to see these stupid fucks gone.

270
00:16:02,482 --> 00:16:03,650
You know that isn't justice.

271
00:16:03,733 --> 00:16:05,402
I have people.

272
00:16:05,485 --> 00:16:08,530
Min-beom, we need to be
on the same page about this.

273
00:16:14,577 --> 00:16:16,037
Then I'll do it my way.

274
00:16:28,049 --> 00:16:29,092
[music fades]

275
00:16:29,676 --> 00:16:32,637
You should know, my dad won bronze
at the Barcelona Olympics,

276
00:16:33,805 --> 00:16:38,101
so I asked him if he happened
to know of a guy named Im Baek-jeong.

277
00:16:39,477 --> 00:16:41,938
Apparently, Im Baek-jeong
was a student to his friend.

278
00:16:42,689 --> 00:16:43,732
Whoa.

279
00:16:45,233 --> 00:16:49,279
He remembered him because he said he was
ambidextrous and had a really good hook.

280
00:16:49,362 --> 00:16:53,199
According to my father, everyone
expected him to become a world champion,

281
00:16:53,283 --> 00:16:57,704
but he's a piece of shit, I guess,
and he totally ruined it for himself.

282
00:16:58,204 --> 00:16:59,039
Mm.

283
00:16:59,122 --> 00:17:00,874
So then, I asked him some more about it

284
00:17:00,957 --> 00:17:03,793
to see if he might be in touch
with the coach who taught Im Baek-jeong.

285
00:17:05,170 --> 00:17:09,090
I mean a coach is the person who would
know almost anything about his boxer.

286
00:17:09,174 --> 00:17:11,468
Go-to moves, weaknesses, all his steps.

287
00:17:11,551 --> 00:17:14,679
That's right. I bet that you'd know
all of my weaknesses.

288
00:17:16,264 --> 00:17:21,561
I, um, watched the video of you fighting
Im Baek-jeong over and over again.

289
00:17:22,312 --> 00:17:24,606
I was thinking about
what kind of advice I could give you

290
00:17:24,689 --> 00:17:26,858
to help you beat him in a fight, and…

291
00:17:27,984 --> 00:17:29,277
[sighs]

292
00:17:30,028 --> 00:17:33,406
I don't think I'm a good enough coach.
I'm at a loss for answers.

293
00:17:34,074 --> 00:17:35,575
I promise it's not your coaching.

294
00:17:35,658 --> 00:17:38,787
I don't know if I've seen an ambidextrous
fighter that could change up his stance.

295
00:17:38,870 --> 00:17:40,163
I just couldn't keep up with him.

296
00:17:41,456 --> 00:17:43,500
Well, his left jab
looked super strong and heavy.

297
00:17:43,583 --> 00:17:46,252
It was. Also, that right hand's fast.

298
00:17:47,504 --> 00:17:50,381
Honestly, I can't really remember
how I fought.

299
00:17:51,216 --> 00:17:53,218
[poignant music playing]

300
00:17:53,968 --> 00:17:58,807
Yeah, so, Gun-woo, how about
we go and get you trained by that coach?

301
00:17:58,890 --> 00:18:00,725
You know, the one
who taught Im Baek-jeong?

302
00:18:01,518 --> 00:18:02,894
This coach could know

303
00:18:03,394 --> 00:18:05,688
the method that might beat Im Baek-jeong.

304
00:18:08,024 --> 00:18:09,859
-Good idea.
-Is it?

305
00:18:10,652 --> 00:18:11,569
I want to win.

306
00:18:14,197 --> 00:18:15,240
[music fades]

307
00:18:15,323 --> 00:18:16,825
Argh. Ow.

308
00:18:16,908 --> 00:18:18,743
-I'm okay, I'm okay.
-What are you doing?

309
00:18:18,827 --> 00:18:19,911
Huh?

310
00:18:20,954 --> 00:18:22,872
-There's food.
-Oh.

311
00:18:35,927 --> 00:18:37,929
-[So-yeon] Eat slowly.
-[Gun-woo] Hmm.

312
00:18:38,471 --> 00:18:39,305
Here.

313
00:18:40,974 --> 00:18:42,183
[gentle music playing]

314
00:18:42,267 --> 00:18:45,854
I don't want you guys to be
getting into something dangerous.

315
00:18:49,941 --> 00:18:52,235
It just breaks my heart
when you guys get hurt.

316
00:18:55,113 --> 00:18:56,573
Don't worry too much, Mom.

317
00:18:56,656 --> 00:18:59,242
How can I not worry
when you're hurt like that?

318
00:19:03,288 --> 00:19:05,039
I'll take better care of him, Mom.

319
00:19:07,584 --> 00:19:08,626
Go ahead.

320
00:19:11,296 --> 00:19:14,174
-Is there any kimchi?
-Just eat your food.

321
00:19:15,133 --> 00:19:16,009
[Gun-woo] Mm.

322
00:19:16,593 --> 00:19:19,637
Let's grab those kimchi noodles
from the convenience store afterwards.

323
00:19:19,721 --> 00:19:21,431
-Pretty much the same thing.
-Let's do that.

324
00:19:22,015 --> 00:19:23,391
[chuckles softly]

325
00:19:23,474 --> 00:19:25,685
Damn, this egg tastes better cold.

326
00:19:26,936 --> 00:19:29,230
[So-yeon] I used
the entire carton of eggs.

327
00:19:29,314 --> 00:19:31,024
Don't eat too fast.

328
00:19:31,107 --> 00:19:32,692
-[Gun-woo] Hmm.
-[So-yeon] Here.

329
00:19:32,775 --> 00:19:34,068
[music stops]

330
00:19:34,152 --> 00:19:37,488
We are currently divided into two teams
that are working in two shifts.

331
00:19:37,572 --> 00:19:42,285
As of now, both Team A and Team B will be
staying on the 16th floor of the hotel.

332
00:19:42,368 --> 00:19:45,371
If we encounter a situation,
both teams can respond together.

333
00:19:46,664 --> 00:19:48,917
So then, how many people is that?

334
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:50,793
There are a total of 12 personnel.

335
00:19:50,877 --> 00:19:53,046
Uh, you can vouch for their skills?

336
00:19:53,129 --> 00:19:54,422
Yes, you don't have to worry.

337
00:19:54,505 --> 00:19:55,423
Ah.

338
00:19:55,506 --> 00:19:57,008
[tense music playing]

339
00:19:58,301 --> 00:19:59,636
Uh, when…

340
00:20:00,386 --> 00:20:01,804
When we take down Im Baek-jeong,

341
00:20:02,764 --> 00:20:05,141
will the Major Crimes Unit be enough?

342
00:20:09,062 --> 00:20:10,438
No, not at all.

343
00:20:11,481 --> 00:20:12,899
Should I call the mobile unit?

344
00:20:13,691 --> 00:20:16,236
Uh, that's not what I meant.

345
00:20:17,654 --> 00:20:21,991
We still don't know who took the money
from Im Baek-jeong, and it's worrying.

346
00:20:23,743 --> 00:20:24,869
[Gang-yong sighs]

347
00:20:24,953 --> 00:20:28,164
Mr. Min, would you like me
to get some Marines?

348
00:20:31,125 --> 00:20:32,377
It wouldn't work.

349
00:20:32,460 --> 00:20:34,128
Oh, yeah. [exhales]

350
00:20:35,046 --> 00:20:36,756
What about the Green Pine Tree Club?

351
00:20:41,594 --> 00:20:42,553
Oh.

352
00:20:43,054 --> 00:20:44,681
Yoon Han-gu, the sergeant?

353
00:20:47,433 --> 00:20:49,936
Is Han-gu in Suwon currently?

354
00:20:50,019 --> 00:20:55,066
Yeah. Baek-jeong's money
shouldn't have gone out that far so…

355
00:20:55,149 --> 00:20:56,276
[snaps fingers]

356
00:20:56,359 --> 00:20:57,986
Okay, I'll reach out to him.

357
00:20:58,069 --> 00:20:59,028
[music stops]

358
00:21:04,951 --> 00:21:06,995
[ominous music playing]

359
00:21:07,078 --> 00:21:08,162
[Man-bae] Hey.

360
00:21:09,789 --> 00:21:10,915
Hey, Diego.

361
00:21:13,376 --> 00:21:15,420
You sure know how to pick a place to meet.

362
00:21:16,587 --> 00:21:18,172
Happy birthday, Captain.

363
00:21:23,845 --> 00:21:25,054
I asked for US dollars.

364
00:21:25,138 --> 00:21:27,724
I'm sorry. I didn't have enough time.

365
00:21:31,769 --> 00:21:34,522
I'm gonna need an extra 10%
when we get to Bangkok.

366
00:21:35,690 --> 00:21:37,692
[tense music playing]

367
00:21:39,610 --> 00:21:41,237
Yeah, fine.

368
00:21:41,738 --> 00:21:43,239
Wednesday, 3 a.m.

369
00:21:45,825 --> 00:21:46,909
[Diego] See you in Cheongju.

370
00:21:47,910 --> 00:21:49,912
Yeah. Okay.

371
00:21:52,415 --> 00:21:53,416
Understood.

372
00:22:00,131 --> 00:22:02,008
Let's get the stitches removed
tomorrow at 10:00.

373
00:22:02,091 --> 00:22:03,051
I'll handle it, sir.

374
00:22:03,134 --> 00:22:05,803
Two nights from now,
Gun-woo's mother will go to the airport.

375
00:22:06,971 --> 00:22:10,141
Say goodbye to your daughter.
It's gonna be a while.

376
00:22:12,810 --> 00:22:14,187
[sighs]

377
00:22:15,646 --> 00:22:16,522
Yes.

378
00:22:20,026 --> 00:22:20,943
[music fades]

379
00:22:22,737 --> 00:22:24,489
[suspenseful music playing]

380
00:22:33,414 --> 00:22:34,415
Han-gu, thanks a lot.

381
00:22:34,499 --> 00:22:37,543
Anything for family.
This is the Violent Crimes Unit.

382
00:22:37,627 --> 00:22:39,545
-[Gang-yong] Hi.
-He's our head detective.

383
00:22:39,629 --> 00:22:42,006
-[Gang-yong] Thank you for coming.
-Nice to meet you.

384
00:22:44,217 --> 00:22:46,803
The owner of the veterinary clinic,
Moon Dong-jo,

385
00:22:46,886 --> 00:22:50,264
has served three prison terms for
manufacturing and distributing narcotics.

386
00:22:50,348 --> 00:22:53,768
He's been practicing illegally
since his license was revoked in 2022.

387
00:22:54,352 --> 00:22:56,062
Here are photos from the site.

388
00:22:59,690 --> 00:23:01,734
Now, let me explain the mission.

389
00:23:01,818 --> 00:23:03,861
Team 1 will wait
at the back door of the clinic,

390
00:23:03,945 --> 00:23:06,280
Team 2 at the restaurant,
and Team 3 at the salon.

391
00:23:06,364 --> 00:23:10,368
Headquarters will give a signal to move in
once the suspect enters the clinic.

392
00:23:10,993 --> 00:23:14,163
Suspects may try to escape
through the back door of the clinic.

393
00:23:14,247 --> 00:23:16,249
Team 1, be as vigilant as possible.

394
00:23:18,418 --> 00:23:21,087
Now, some key info.

395
00:23:21,170 --> 00:23:23,548
Trust only the people in this room.

396
00:23:23,631 --> 00:23:26,843
If you see any unexpected backup,
be on your guard.

397
00:23:29,637 --> 00:23:32,265
It's possible there are cops
who've been bought.

398
00:23:33,015 --> 00:23:36,936
Let's work together and show them all
what great cops are really made of.

399
00:23:37,019 --> 00:23:38,104
[all] Yes, sir!

400
00:23:38,771 --> 00:23:39,772
[music fades]

401
00:23:56,247 --> 00:23:58,249
[tense music playing]

402
00:24:04,755 --> 00:24:07,925
Oh shit. Motherfucker.

403
00:24:11,679 --> 00:24:12,722
[sighs]

404
00:24:13,764 --> 00:24:15,683
MOON DONG-JO VETERINARY CLINIC

405
00:24:17,643 --> 00:24:19,645
[Gang-yong] Team 1,
you're in position, right?

406
00:24:19,729 --> 00:24:20,938
Team 1, in position.

407
00:24:21,522 --> 00:24:22,356
Team 2?

408
00:24:23,441 --> 00:24:24,567
Team 2, copy.

409
00:24:25,735 --> 00:24:26,944
[Gang-yong] Team 3?

410
00:24:27,695 --> 00:24:28,905
[Han-gu] All clear.

411
00:24:28,988 --> 00:24:30,281
[music subsides]

412
00:24:36,746 --> 00:24:38,539
Vehicle approaching. Stand by, stand by.

413
00:24:42,710 --> 00:24:44,962
[car approaches]

414
00:24:52,720 --> 00:24:55,806
[suspenseful music playing]

415
00:25:08,611 --> 00:25:09,820
-[device beeps]
-Action!

416
00:25:09,904 --> 00:25:11,489
-[man 1] Let's go.
-[man 2] Go, go, go!

417
00:25:12,698 --> 00:25:14,492
[tense music playing]

418
00:25:14,575 --> 00:25:15,576
[grunts]

419
00:25:22,542 --> 00:25:24,669
-[man 2] Freeze! Don't move!
-[man 1] Get him!

420
00:25:24,752 --> 00:25:26,003
[man 3] Police!

421
00:25:26,087 --> 00:25:27,588
-[man 2] Get his ass!
-[man 4] Come out!

422
00:25:27,672 --> 00:25:28,589
Shit.

423
00:25:28,673 --> 00:25:30,383
[men grunting]

424
00:25:36,806 --> 00:25:37,890
[man 5] Im Baek-jeong.

425
00:25:38,683 --> 00:25:40,101
Put your hands in the air.

426
00:25:40,893 --> 00:25:42,895
-[music intensifies]
-[men grunting]

427
00:25:46,399 --> 00:25:47,858
[man 6 grunts] Ugh! Ugh! Ugh! Ugh!

428
00:25:49,110 --> 00:25:50,278
[groaning]

429
00:25:50,361 --> 00:25:51,362
[man 1 groans]

430
00:25:54,740 --> 00:25:55,866
[man 5] You fucking bastard!

431
00:25:55,950 --> 00:25:58,369
-[knife slicing]
-[man 5 groans]

432
00:26:03,916 --> 00:26:05,126
Son of a bitch!

433
00:26:05,960 --> 00:26:07,086
Stay still!

434
00:26:08,838 --> 00:26:09,839
[knife slices]

435
00:26:09,922 --> 00:26:11,632
[screams]

436
00:26:16,804 --> 00:26:19,181
[Taser rattles]

437
00:26:19,265 --> 00:26:20,433
Shoot his ass!

438
00:26:20,516 --> 00:26:22,101
[Taser rattles]

439
00:26:22,184 --> 00:26:23,394
[wheezes]

440
00:26:24,854 --> 00:26:26,731
-[Baek-jeong groans]
-[man 3] Get him!

441
00:26:27,440 --> 00:26:29,483
[Han-gu] You have the right
to remain silent.

442
00:26:29,567 --> 00:26:32,236
Anything that you say
can and will be used against you.

443
00:26:32,320 --> 00:26:33,487
Now, get up!

444
00:26:33,571 --> 00:26:34,822
[music stops]

445
00:26:34,905 --> 00:26:36,365
Don't fucking move.

446
00:26:37,825 --> 00:26:39,118
Stay right there.

447
00:26:40,536 --> 00:26:41,829
I'm Min Gang-yong.

448
00:26:43,205 --> 00:26:45,166
I'm gonna make sure that you rot in jail.

449
00:26:47,335 --> 00:26:49,295
[gentle music playing]

450
00:26:52,673 --> 00:26:54,550
[Mr. Moon claps] Yes!

451
00:26:54,634 --> 00:26:55,676
Yeah!

452
00:27:02,558 --> 00:27:04,393
-[sighs deeply]
-[door slides closed]

453
00:27:11,942 --> 00:27:13,653
[tense music playing]

454
00:27:21,869 --> 00:27:23,704
[shuddering]

455
00:27:39,553 --> 00:27:40,846
[man] What are you doing?

456
00:27:41,514 --> 00:27:43,307
Tell me what're you doing!

457
00:27:46,644 --> 00:27:52,775
Why should I go on doing this?

458
00:27:53,401 --> 00:27:54,276
[exhales]

459
00:27:57,446 --> 00:27:59,198
How much you want, huh?

460
00:27:59,281 --> 00:28:01,325
Five Bitcoins. Got it?

461
00:28:01,409 --> 00:28:03,661
-You want 500 million won for this?
-Yeah.

462
00:28:06,539 --> 00:28:07,581
[scoffs]

463
00:28:08,207 --> 00:28:09,125
[chuckles]

464
00:28:09,875 --> 00:28:11,001
Shit!

465
00:28:22,304 --> 00:28:23,764
-I sent it.
-[phone buzzes]

466
00:28:29,603 --> 00:28:31,063
Thank you for the payment.

467
00:28:34,191 --> 00:28:39,739
[sirens wailing]

468
00:28:40,948 --> 00:28:42,074
BLOODHOUNDS : SEOUL

469
00:28:43,868 --> 00:28:45,828
-[phone rings]
-[man] Son of a bitch.

470
00:28:45,911 --> 00:28:46,829
Oh, just hit it.

471
00:28:46,912 --> 00:28:48,205
STAREX FROM CLINIC TO POLICE

472
00:28:48,289 --> 00:28:49,165
EXTRACTION, 200 MIL

473
00:28:49,749 --> 00:28:51,792
Let's go make some money.
It's 200 million. Hurry up!

474
00:28:51,876 --> 00:28:53,043
Let's fucking go!

475
00:28:53,753 --> 00:28:54,962
[phone chimes]

476
00:28:59,049 --> 00:29:00,092
[chuckles]

477
00:29:01,802 --> 00:29:02,762
[phone beeps]

478
00:29:03,596 --> 00:29:04,930
[phone buzzes]

479
00:29:13,355 --> 00:29:15,065
FROM MOON DONG-JO VETERINARY CLINIC

480
00:29:15,149 --> 00:29:17,193
STAREX VAN TO NATIONAL POLICE AGENCY

481
00:29:17,276 --> 00:29:18,861
SAVE MY COLLEAGUES, 200 MIL

482
00:29:20,112 --> 00:29:21,739
MOON DONG-JO VETERINARY CLINIC

483
00:29:25,785 --> 00:29:27,787
[suspenseful music playing]

484
00:29:40,800 --> 00:29:42,009
[detective] What's that?

485
00:29:44,094 --> 00:29:45,262
What's going on?

486
00:29:45,346 --> 00:29:47,389
-Ah, shit!
-[horn honking]

487
00:29:47,473 --> 00:29:48,474
Fucking hell.

488
00:29:52,812 --> 00:29:54,188
[engine revs]

489
00:29:54,271 --> 00:29:56,023
-[horn honking]
-[detective groans]

490
00:29:56,106 --> 00:29:57,650
[tires screech]

491
00:29:57,733 --> 00:29:59,401
Hey, get out of the fucking way!

492
00:30:01,695 --> 00:30:03,322
[passing car horn blaring]

493
00:30:04,365 --> 00:30:06,033
Whoa, shit!

494
00:30:09,036 --> 00:30:10,162
[grunts]

495
00:30:12,581 --> 00:30:15,251
-What now?
-Let's just get out of here.

496
00:30:16,669 --> 00:30:19,255
Requesting backup here at Jinho Bridge.
Car accident. Car accident.

497
00:30:19,338 --> 00:30:21,340
[tense music playing]

498
00:30:24,343 --> 00:30:26,095
[detective] Shit. Shit.

499
00:30:26,178 --> 00:30:29,682
[men bellowing] Ah!

500
00:30:30,182 --> 00:30:33,811
-[man 1] Come on! Come on!
-Open it! Get the fucking door! Come on!

501
00:30:33,894 --> 00:30:36,230
-[man 2] Yeah!
-[man 1] Open the fucking door! Get out!

502
00:30:36,814 --> 00:30:37,648
[man 3 yelps]

503
00:30:39,733 --> 00:30:41,735
[man 4] Come on. Get in there. Let's go!

504
00:30:43,612 --> 00:30:44,697
-[groans]
-[Taser rattles]

505
00:30:44,780 --> 00:30:45,823
Oh shit.

506
00:30:48,117 --> 00:30:49,326
Come here!

507
00:30:50,494 --> 00:30:53,080
[engine revs]

508
00:30:54,039 --> 00:30:54,915
